HEADWORD: Amaryllideous
<hw>Am`a*ryl*lid"e*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or resembling, an order of
plants differing from the lily family chiefly in having the ovary below
the petals. The narcissus and daffodil are members of this
family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amaryllis</ent>⟦br⟧
